"There is one week left to apply for P-EBT food benefits. You should have received a school email or letter with a link to the application. P-EBT is for children who received SNAP March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. If you have not received information from your school, please contact 833-613-6220. Visit hhs.texas.gov/PEBT for more information."

post_text:
RISD Families,

We will remain in the home based learning model until May 4th as mandated by Governor Abbott.
We will continue our food service, although new guidelines state that we can only feed whenever we were going to have school. Therefore we will not be sending home food for the weekend any more.
We are still following our school calendar and will observe our days off for our staff and students.
We are moving to be 100% online for all of our students with their work.
Thank you for your help and flexibility as we work together to take care of our students, staff and community.

#AngoraStrong

"Dear Parent/Guardian:

Rocksprings Elementary and Jr. High will be testing for its Gifted and Talented Program. If you think your child might benefit from such a program, we would welcome your nomination. Identification is based on a number of different criteria, with selection being made by a committee of educators. Should you wish to nominate your child, the forms may be obtained at the Rocksprings Elementary School office between 8:00 ‚Äì 3:30 P.M. Nomination forms must be completed and returned to your child‚Äôs classroom teacher by September 13, 2019.

Thanks for your time and consideration,

Carla Worrell
G/T Coordinator"

Go Red Go!!!

A message from the Gilmer Library and Camp Eagle!:

"What: Camp Eagle Sign-Up
Where: Gilmer Memorial Library
When: Tuesday, April 2nd
*The Camp Eagle staff will be here from 3:30-5:30 for sign-up!
Come to the Gilmer Memorial Library to meet with Camp Eagle staff to sign your kids up for an action-packed, adventure-filled week of summer camp right down the road! The discounted summer camp for Rocksprings residents is the week of June 2nd-8th for boys and girls finishing 1st-7th grades. Any 8th-12th graders are welcome to come to find out more about individual scholarships for camp that week as well! "What: Camp Eagle Sign-Up
Where: Gilmer Memorial Library
When: Tuesday, April 2nd
*The Camp Eagle staff will be here from 3:30-5:30 for sign-up!
Come to the Gilmer Memorial Library to meet with Camp Eagle staff to sign your kids up for an action-packed, adventure-filled week of summer camp right down the road! Any 8th-12th graders are welcome to come to find out more about individual scholarships for camp that week as well! Camp Eagle normally costs $800 for the week, but Camp Eagle welcomes local Rocksprings kids to come for just $50!"

Dear Parents,
I am proud to announce that we will be conducting STAAR Benchmark Testing next week, March 4-8, 2019. The purpose of the testing next week is to gauge our preparedness and readiness for formal testing that will take place in April and May 2019 of this school year. Our Benchmark Testing will be for students in Grades 3 through 10.

Next week will be a challenging week at RISD with Benchmark Testing taking place, extra duties and assignments for many teachers and faculty members, several extra-curricular events involving many of our students, and the RISD Spring Break scheduled for March 11-15. We ask that all parents help make certain your child is on time and prepared for school every day and gets plenty of rest each day next week!

Thank you for all that you do to support our students, faculty and staff, and Rocksprings ISD!

Sincerely,

Brian McCraw, M.Ed.
Principal, Rocksprings ISD

post_text:
Dear Parents, February 4, 2019

Rocksprings ISD would like to remind parents about student illnesses. If your child has vomiting, diarrhea or fever of 99 degrees or higher PLEASE DO NOT SEND THEM TO SCHOOL. As of today, we have several different types of viral stomach strains around the school. We also have two cases of POSITIVE FLU. If your child is sick or is experiencing flu-like symptoms, the CDC recommends that you keep them home for at least 24 hours after their fever has dissipated, except to get medical care or for other necessities. (Evidence of fever should be absent for 24 hours without the use of a fever-reducing medicine BEFORE they can return to school.)

Thank You,

Shanna Fowler-McDonald

School Nurse
